    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary, and if you like your steak well-done, it may take you a little longer than 10 mins</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/steak-salad-with-chipotle-and-orange-dressing/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of\u00a0<strong>vegetable oil\u00a0</strong>over a high heat</p><p>Pat the\u00a0<strong>rump steaks</strong>\u00a0dry with\u00a0kitchen\u00a0paper</p><p>Drizzle them with\u00a0<strong>vegetable oil</strong>\u00a0and season all over with\u00a0<strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong>, the <strong>ground cumin</strong> and <strong>dried oregano </strong>\u2013 these are your<strong> spice crusted steaks</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/steak-salad-with-chipotle-and-orange-dressing/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once very hot, add the<strong> spice crusted steaks\u00a0</strong>to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 2-3 min on each side; for medium, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p><p>Once the steaks are cooked, transfer them to a plate to rest</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/steak-salad-with-chipotle-and-orange-dressing/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a bowl with the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and juice of the <strong>orange<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Add 3 tbsp\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[5 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix\u00a0it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>chipotle & orange dressing</strong></p><p>Tip: Taste the dressing and add a pinch of sugar if it needs it</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/steak-salad-with-chipotle-and-orange-dressing/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half and season them with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/steak-salad-with-chipotle-and-orange-dressing/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain\u00a0and rinse the<strong> black beans</strong></p><p>Once the steaks done, wipe out the steak pan with kitchen paper and return it to\u00a0a medium heat</p><p>Add the<strong> drained black beans</strong>\u00a0and\u00a0<strong>soy sauce</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/steak-salad-with-chipotle-and-orange-dressing/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested steaks</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/steak-salad-with-chipotle-and-orange-dressing/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide\u00a0the<strong>\u00a0baby leaf salad</strong>,<strong>\u00a0warmed black beans </strong>and<strong> halved cherry tomatoes\u00a0</strong>between your plates, add some\u00a0<strong>chipotle & orange\u00a0dressing</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Top with the <strong>sliced steak\u00a0</strong>and\u00a0crumble over the<strong> feta</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chipotle & orange dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
